title: For Sale/Trade:  1976 Chevrolet K-20 3/4 Ton 4x4 - DANA 44, 350 Chevy
postcontent:
I have a 1976 Chevrolet K20 4x4 for sale. Starts, runs, idols and drives in 2 wheel and in 4 wheel GREAT!! 

It has a 350ci engine, auto trans, 203 transfer case with shaft kit for part time four wheel, DANA 44 rear, 14 bolt front with full floater 8 lug axles. The transfer case was rebuilt when the shaft kit was installed. The shaft kit allows the NP203 transfer case to now have 5 positions. High, High Lock, Low, Low Lock and Neutral. There are no hubs to mess with or anything. Everything is done from the drivers seat. The engine bottom and top end was recently rebuilt and it has a new Edelbrock Performer intake with new Holly 600 carb. The muffler and tailpipe was recently replaced as it was stock. It has rust spots and patched holes and the body has a lot of dents. The truck only really rusted in the common areas for that year model. The cab corners are completely solid, the floor pans have very little rust and are still very solid for being original. The hood mounts are in great shape, the hood opens and closes without any problems. This truck was used as a farm/woods truck for and is by no means a show piece but mechanically is in great shape. Could easily be used as a daily driver. All of the glass is there, no cracks or chips. It also has new shocks, fuel pump, battery, plugs, and wires. It is on 35" tires that have about 30% tread left. Breaks were done about 2000 miles ago. Headlights (high and low beam), wipers and dash lights work great. Transmission shifts very well and does not slip or stick. 

Aside from looks, this truck is very mechanically sound. The only thing that does not work is the radio. I have the original title and it is registered and insured in my name. I drive it to work and back a couple times a week just for fun.

Bed is diamond plate steel covered, and the rear bumper is new.

Can send more pics if requested.

Asking $1300obo.
